OL,3,CNew independent regulator 'must tackle
OL,4,Cissue of dementia in football'
OL,6,FThe prevalence of dementia in football
OL,7,Fmust be tackled by the sport's new
OL,8,Findependent regulator, MPs have said.
OL,10,FThere are calls for the new watchdog
OL,11,Fto be given powers to investigate the
OL,12,Fissue or risk current players
OL,13,Fsuffering the same fate as England
OL,14,Fstars of the past like Sir Bobby
OL,15,FCharlton and Nobby Stiles.
OL,17,FCharlton's dementia diagnosis was
OL,18,Fconfirmed in November 2020, weeks
OL,19,Fafter the death of his 1966 World Cup-
OL,20,Fwinning team-mate Stiles.
